From 6466e30f568342a8d25eadd638b5b052d04916d2 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <claude@anthropic.com>
Date: Sat, 18 Jul 2026 18:53:13 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] feat: leaderboard period filter + personal rank endpoint,
 plus test coverage
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Backend gaps closed (backlog #6):
- GET /users/leaderboard now supports period=semaine|mois|global in addition
  to filiere. Previously only filiere filtering existed; week/month didn't
  exist at all despite being in the backlog. Period ranking sums XP from
  exercise attempts and contest answers by timestamp; global ranking uses
  xpTotal directly (and so is the only view that includes forum XP, which
  has no dated ledger to filter by — noted in the code).
- New GET /users/me/rank endpoint (also period/filiere aware) — backlog #6.2
  called for a personal-rank display but no backend support existed for it
  at all, despite the tracking sheet marking it done.
- getLeaderboard now excludes ADMIN accounts from the ranking (previously
  admins would show up on the student leaderboard).

Test coverage added (previously zero for these):
- forum.service.ts / forum.controller.ts — full coverage (listing, filtering,
  post/reply creation with XP awarding incl. the settings-lookup-failure
  fallback, like/unlike toggle, reporting).
- auth.controller.ts — routing/delegation coverage for all six endpoints.
- users.service.ts / users.controller.ts — rewritten to cover the new period
  and personal-rank behavior alongside the existing profile tests.

Full suite: 20/20 test suites, 156/156 tests passing (verified against a
local Prisma client stub, as usual in this sandbox — run against your real
migrated database to be sure, same as the last patch).
